{
  "texts": [
    "Interpretability refers to the degree to which one can assign qualitative meaning to the scores or changes in scores 71.",
    "I included an assessment of overall scores' distributions, missing data, and floor and ceiling effects.",
    "Overall scores' distributions show if the scale results in normally distributed data.",
    "Missing data should be minimized to ensure they did not affect the validation procedure.",
    "Finally, floor and ceiling effects show whether the extreme items are missing in the lower or upper end of the scale, indicating limited content validity."
  ]
}